# =============================================================================
# Stochastic Transit Router - Git Attributes Configuration
# Line Ending, Binary, and Diff Management for Version Control
#
# This file configures how Git handles line endings, binary files, and
# other version control attributes across the repository. It ensures:
# - Consistent line endings (LF) across all platforms (Windows, macOS, Linux)
# - Proper binary file handling to prevent corruption
# - Correct diff display for different file types
# - Language-specific merge strategies where applicable
#
# Documentation: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitattributes
# =============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# GLOBAL CONFIGURATION - DEFAULT BEHAVIOR
# ============================================================================

# Default: Auto-detect text files and use LF line endings (Unix standard)
# This prevents CRLF line endings on Windows from being committed
* text=auto eol=lf

# ============================================================================
# SOURCE CODE FILES - TEXT WITH LINE ENDING NORMALIZATION
# ============================================================================

# ------ Python Files (.py) ------
*.py text eol=lf diff=python
*.pyi text eol=lf diff=python

# ------ Shell Scripts (.sh, .bash) ------
*.sh text eol=lf diff=bash
*.bash text eol=lf diff=bash
*.zsh text eol=lf diff=bash

# ------ Batch/PowerShell Scripts ------
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf diff=powershell

# ------ Markdown Documentation (.md) ------
*.md text eol=lf diff=markdown

# ------ Configuration Files (Text) ------
*.yaml text eol=lf diff=yaml
*.yml text eol=lf diff=yaml
*.toml text eol=lf diff=toml
*.ini text eol=lf
*.cfg text eol=lf
*.conf text eol=lf

# ------ JSON Files ------
